# %% :::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::: FUNCTION 4 ::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::: #
# decompose a number with more than max_digits digits into blocks with less than max_digits digits
def decomposer(number, max_digits=4300):
    block_size = 10**max_digits
    
    # base case
    if number < block_size: return [number]
    
    block = number // block_size # take the first max_digits digits
    rest = number % block_size # the rest of the number
    
    return [block] + decomposer(rest, max_digits)
